div.div:
Abstract directed acyclic graph of operations (flow_graph). Portable, flexible. Numeric placeholders for input/output.
Separate (flow_job) structure for associating I/O interfaces and configuration.
Context object used for all API calls - stores error codes and stack traces.

div.div: If we previously forced estimation across whitespace/face nodes, we have to throw away

this copy of the graph and start over before executing for real. At this stage only metadata has been parsed from
images, so failing fast is very possible. Estimation lets is also pre-allocate a slab, if we want to.
